| Govt. Report Slams FBI's Internal Network Security                 |
|   from the uncle-sam's-open-doors dept.                            |
|   posted by CowboyNeal on Friday May 25, @02:44 (Security)         |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/25/0357230           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "The Government Accountability Office, the
federal government's watchdog agency, Thursday [0]released a report
critical of the FBI's internal network, asserting it lacks security
controls adequate to thwart an insider attack. Among its other findings,
the GAO said the FBI did not adequately "identify and authenticate users
to prevent unauthorized access." The GAO report also criticized FBI
network security in other regards, saying that there was a lack of
encryption to protect sensitive data and patch management wasn't being
done in a timely manner."

Discuss this story at:
    http://it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/25/0357230

Links:
    0. http://www.networkworld.com/news/2007/052407-gao-slams-fbi-network-security.html


